WEBVTT

00:01.876 --> 00:04.879
[adventurous music]

00:04.963 --> 00:12.971
♪ ♪

00:33.366 --> 00:35.368
[suspenseful music]

00:35.452 --> 00:44.210
♪ ♪

00:52.010 --> 00:53.762
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:53.845 --> 00:54.846
WELL?

00:54.929 --> 00:57.474
SPEAK UP.

00:57.557 --> 00:59.642
- WE SAW THE DOOR WAS OPEN,
SO WE JUST CAME IN.

00:59.726 --> 01:01.811
- AND THEN WE HEARD NOISES.

01:01.895 --> 01:04.480
- YEAH, AND--AND LIBRARIES
ARE THE MOST HAUNTED PLACES

01:04.563 --> 01:05.815
NEXT TO ATTICS
AND DESERTED HIGHWAYS, SO--

01:05.899 --> 01:08.318
- THERE'S NO SPOOKS HERE.

01:08.401 --> 01:10.487
BUT YOU STILL CAN'T WANDER
AROUND DESERTED AREAS.

01:10.570 --> 01:11.613
GO ON, BACK TO YOUR HOUSE.

01:11.696 --> 01:15.158
- AH, BAGS.

01:26.711 --> 01:28.880
GO.

01:32.425 --> 01:36.679
INSTIGATE A BAG AND LOCKER
SEARCH OF THE ENTIRE SCHOOL.

01:36.763 --> 01:38.389
WE MUST FIND THAT MISSING BOOK.

01:38.473 --> 01:40.016
- VICTOR,
WE ARE THE FIRST PEOPLE

01:40.099 --> 01:42.352
TO SET FOOT IN THIS LIBRARY
FOR YEARS.

01:42.435 --> 01:44.145
WHOEVER TOOK THAT BOOK
TOOK IT A LONG TIME AGO.

01:44.229 --> 01:46.815
- THAT BOOK
IS OUR ONE HOPE FOR THE ELIXIR,

01:46.898 --> 01:49.943
AND I WILL NOT GIVE IT UP.

01:53.947 --> 01:56.574
- OH, I'M SO PROUD OF YOU.

01:56.658 --> 01:57.867
COME TO PAPA.

01:57.951 --> 02:00.578
- ALFIE, THERE WON'T BE ANY LEFT
AT THIS RATE.

02:00.662 --> 02:04.040
- [whimpers]

02:04.123 --> 02:06.543
- THEY WERE TALKING
ABOUT THE ELIXIR, FABIAN.

02:06.626 --> 02:09.044
VICTOR OBVIOUSLY HASN'T HUNG UP
HIS EVIL BOOTS YET.

02:09.127 --> 02:11.381
- BUT YOU HEARD
WHAT SWEETY SAID.

02:11.464 --> 02:13.800
THEY DON'T HAVE THE RECIPE,
AND THE CUP WAS DESTROYED.

02:13.883 --> 02:17.554
- YEAH, ABOUT THE CUP.

02:17.637 --> 02:19.973
- WHAT IS THAT AMAZING SMELL?

02:21.808 --> 02:25.395
- GIVE THAT A MIX.

02:25.478 --> 02:26.980
- SOMETHING SMELLS NICE.

02:27.063 --> 02:29.232
- YEAH, I'M, UH,
HELPING TRUDY COOK SUPPER.

02:29.315 --> 02:30.984
- AFTER LAST TIME?

02:31.067 --> 02:35.530
NO ONE'S FORGOTTEN
YOUR MARSHMALLOW MEAT SURPRISE.

02:35.613 --> 02:38.032
- DELICIOUS.

02:38.116 --> 02:39.993
[blender whirring]

02:40.076 --> 02:41.744
- ALFIE!

02:41.828 --> 02:44.289
OH, TURN IT OFF.

02:44.372 --> 02:44.873
- [laughs]

02:44.956 --> 02:47.250
- OH, IN THE--

02:47.333 --> 02:48.459
- SARAH WOULD KNOW WHAT TO DO.

02:48.543 --> 02:51.588
I WISH I COULD MAKE MYSELF
DREAM OF HER AGAIN.

02:51.671 --> 02:54.132
- I TRIED TO MAKE MYSELF DREAM
ABOUT JUSTIN BIEBER ONCE,

02:54.215 --> 02:54.841
EXCEPT IT WASN'T JUSTIN BIEBER.

02:54.924 --> 02:56.342
IT WAS JUST A BEAVER.

02:59.470 --> 03:01.097
I PUT THAT DOWN TO A BRAIN TYPO.

03:01.180 --> 03:03.141
- AMBER,
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

03:03.224 --> 03:04.767
- WHY?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

03:04.851 --> 03:05.768
- DREAMS.

03:05.852 --> 03:07.145
- ME TOO.

03:07.228 --> 03:07.937
I'LL LEND YOU THIS BOOK I HAVE.

03:08.021 --> 03:11.107
IT'S REALLY GOOD.

03:11.190 --> 03:13.067
- OH, UH--

03:15.278 --> 03:17.989
- AND THEN NEXT,
COUNT YOUR BREATHS,

03:18.072 --> 03:19.741
AND WITH EACH BREATH,

03:19.824 --> 03:21.951
IMAGINE YOURSELF WALKING
DOWN A STAIRCASE,

03:22.035 --> 03:24.871
ONE STEP AT A TIME.

03:24.954 --> 03:27.290
AND THEN THE BEAVER--
I MEAN, BIEBER--

03:27.373 --> 03:29.500
IS WAITING FOR YOU
AT THE BOTTOM.

03:29.584 --> 03:30.960
[knock at door]

03:31.044 --> 03:32.045
- HERE WE GO, AMBER,

03:32.128 --> 03:33.630
THE FIRST GIFT OF MANY.

03:33.713 --> 03:37.133
- OH, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

03:37.216 --> 03:39.010
HOW MANY, EXACTLY?

03:39.093 --> 03:42.555
- IT'S 10:00.

03:42.639 --> 03:44.515
- GOT TO GO.

03:44.599 --> 03:46.142
- YOU'LL HAVE TIME--

03:46.225 --> 03:48.102
- CUPCAKES, YUMMY!

03:48.186 --> 03:54.067
- AND THEN I WANT TO HEAR
A PIN...

03:54.150 --> 03:54.817
DROP.

03:54.901 --> 03:57.153
- SORRY, SORRY.

03:57.236 --> 03:57.779
JUST DOING THE ROUNDS UP THERE,
YOU KNOW.

03:57.862 --> 04:00.406
OKAY, CARRY ON.

04:13.002 --> 04:15.755
- FIVE, FOUR, THREE,

04:15.838 --> 04:18.298
TWO, ONE.

04:18.382 --> 04:19.841
HELLO?

04:19.926 --> 04:20.885
SARAH?

04:20.969 --> 04:25.056
ARE YOU THERE?

04:25.139 --> 04:26.599
I NEED YOUR HELP.

04:26.683 --> 04:28.434
SARAH?

04:33.731 --> 04:34.857
[gasps]

04:34.941 --> 04:37.068
- DRY YOUR EYES, CHOSEN ONE.

04:43.074 --> 04:45.827
- I STILL NEED YOU, SARAH.

04:45.910 --> 04:48.871
[eerie music]

04:48.955 --> 04:56.796
♪ ♪

05:00.591 --> 05:01.926
- IT WON'T FIT IN THE--

05:02.010 --> 05:04.554
- [gasps and screams]

05:04.637 --> 05:05.888
- [screams]

05:05.972 --> 05:08.599
- AMBER, YOUR FACE.

05:08.683 --> 05:10.018
- [screams]

05:10.101 --> 05:12.729
- WHAT?
WHERE'S THE INTRUDER?

05:12.812 --> 05:14.439
AH!

05:16.649 --> 05:21.529
- SO, AMBER,
TALK ME THROUGH THE NEW 'DO.

05:24.657 --> 05:26.993
- ALFIE LEWIS, LOOK AT MY FACE.

05:27.076 --> 05:29.454
- BEAUTIFUL AS EVER, UM--

05:29.537 --> 05:30.413
both: OH!

05:30.496 --> 05:31.456
- IT'S NOT THAT BAD.

05:31.539 --> 05:32.498
IS IT THAT BAD?

05:32.582 --> 05:33.875
- AMBER,
YOU LOOK LIKE A BALLOON ANIMAL.

05:33.958 --> 05:36.252
- I KNEW IT.

05:36.335 --> 05:38.171
- AMBER, YOU KNOW I LOVE YOU
FOR YOUR INNER BEAUTY,

05:38.254 --> 05:40.089
AND NO MATTER WHAT
DEFORMING ILLNESS YOU MAY HAVE,

05:40.173 --> 05:41.049
I'LL ALWAYS--

05:41.132 --> 05:42.425
- IT'S YOU, YOU DOOFUS!

05:42.508 --> 05:44.260
I'M ALLERGIC TO RASPBERRIES,

05:44.343 --> 05:46.596
AND YOU MADE ME
RASPBERRY-FLAVORED CUPCAKES.

05:46.679 --> 05:48.097
- OH.

05:48.181 --> 05:49.057
[bell rings]

05:49.140 --> 05:51.893
- YES, PERFECT TIMING.

05:51.976 --> 05:54.604
- TELL ME THE TRUTH.

05:54.687 --> 05:56.064
HAIR?

05:56.147 --> 05:57.273
OR NO HAIR?

05:57.356 --> 05:59.609
- HAIR.
- DEFINITELY HAIR.

06:01.235 --> 06:02.111
THERE WE GO.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.279
THIS WILL CHEER YOU UP, AMBER.

06:03.362 --> 06:05.198
- WHAT IS IT?
- FLOWERS.

06:05.281 --> 06:06.783
- AH!

06:06.866 --> 06:09.202
OW, OW, OW, OW!

06:15.041 --> 06:17.043
IT'S A CACTUS.

06:17.126 --> 06:18.002
YOU GOT ME A CACTUS.

06:18.086 --> 06:22.131
- GIFT FAIL, ALFIE.

06:22.215 --> 06:23.716
- WHAT HAPPENED TO ORCHIDS?

06:23.800 --> 06:25.843
- OH, CACTI WERE TWO-FOR-ONE.

06:25.927 --> 06:27.637
- WELL, WHERE'S THE OTHER ONE?

06:27.720 --> 06:28.930
[screams]

06:29.013 --> 06:31.390
- OH, GOOD.
YOU FOUND IT.

06:31.474 --> 06:32.725
[laughs]

06:32.809 --> 06:34.018
LOOK AT YOU.

06:34.102 --> 06:36.938
- NO MORE GIFTS, ALFIE.

06:37.021 --> 06:38.481
WHEN I SAID YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE,

06:38.564 --> 06:41.109
YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T HAVE.

06:48.866 --> 06:50.159
- I SAID SIX.

06:50.243 --> 06:51.369
- THAT'S ALL THEY HAD
IN THE SHOP.

06:51.452 --> 06:53.204
WHY DO YOU NEED SO MANY?

06:53.287 --> 06:56.374
- TO MAKE FRIENDS
AND INFLUENCE PEOPLE.

06:56.457 --> 06:57.166
THIS STUFF IS LIKE CURRENCY
ON THE INSIDE.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.418
- THIS ISN'T ALCATRAZ.

06:59.502 --> 07:01.671
- OH, AND I WANT
HALF YOUR ALLOWANCE.

07:01.754 --> 07:04.507
UNLESS YOU WANT ME
TO BLOW THE WHISTLE.

07:04.590 --> 07:06.467
- OKAY.
OKAY.

07:06.551 --> 07:07.468
- PLEASURE DOING BUSINESS
WITH YOU, CLARKE.

07:16.936 --> 07:17.562
- OF COURSE, YOU MUST STAY.

07:17.645 --> 07:19.480
- OH, YOU ARE SO KIND.

07:19.564 --> 07:19.897
THANK YOU, I--

07:19.981 --> 07:22.358
- GRAN!

07:22.441 --> 07:24.944
- OH, HI, DARLING.

07:25.027 --> 07:28.948
OH, MISS ME ALREADY?

07:29.031 --> 07:30.032
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

07:30.116 --> 07:32.410
- YEAH, OF COURSE.

07:32.493 --> 07:35.163
ARE--ARE YOU OKAY?

07:35.246 --> 07:36.539
WHAT'S WITH ALL THE LUGGAGE?

07:36.622 --> 07:38.207
- JUST MY LUCK TO PICK A HOTEL
THAT FLOODS.

07:38.291 --> 07:39.667
- AND EVERYWHERE ELSE IS FULL,

07:39.750 --> 07:42.879
SO I THOUGHT YOUR GRAN
COULD STAY IN YOUR ROOM TONIGHT,

07:42.962 --> 07:44.297
IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

07:44.380 --> 07:46.382
- YOU KNOW, I'M KIND OF GLAD
YOUR HOTEL FLOODED.

07:46.465 --> 07:47.383
- SO AM I.

07:47.466 --> 07:48.342
- COME.

07:48.426 --> 07:49.635
- OH, OKAY.

07:49.719 --> 07:53.639
HERE'S ONE OF ME
WITH A REALLY BIG BUTTRESS.

07:53.723 --> 07:56.142
- OH, NOW,
DON'T PUT YOURSELF DOWN.

07:56.225 --> 07:58.811
[together] SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

07:58.895 --> 08:01.063
- YOU DO REALIZE YOU'RE GOING
TO SPEND THE ENTIRE FILM

08:01.147 --> 08:02.064
EXPLAINING THE PLOT TO HIM.

08:02.148 --> 08:03.357
- SHUT UP, CLARKE.

08:03.441 --> 08:06.527
UH, ARE YOU SURE YOU CAN'T COME?

08:06.611 --> 08:09.822
- LOOK AT THESE GARGOYLES,
FABIAN.

08:09.906 --> 08:11.532
- NINA MARTIN, FABIAN RUTTER.
OH--

08:16.662 --> 08:18.831
- OOH, WAS THAT HIM?

08:18.915 --> 08:20.583
<i>THE</i> VICTOR?

08:20.666 --> 08:21.918
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
HE WAS CUTE?

08:22.001 --> 08:24.629
[laughter]

08:24.712 --> 08:26.088
I THINK HE IS.

08:29.008 --> 08:32.053
- [snoring]

08:34.347 --> 08:36.849
[suspenseful music]

08:36.933 --> 08:37.850
thunk!

08:37.933 --> 08:40.144
- [gasps]

08:40.227 --> 08:43.773
- [continues snoring]

08:43.856 --> 08:51.614
♪ ♪

08:54.283 --> 08:56.410
- [chuckling]

08:56.494 --> 09:00.581
- I KNOW IT'S NOT AS GOOD
AS A MOVIE AND POPCORN, BUT--

09:00.665 --> 09:03.834
[laughs]

09:03.918 --> 09:06.462
- LOOK, IT'S PERFECT.

09:06.545 --> 09:07.713
IF IT WASN'T FOR THIS ATTIC,

09:07.797 --> 09:09.507
WE MIGHT HAVE NEVER
EVEN GOT TOGETHER.

09:09.590 --> 09:14.095
- I GUESS,
WHEN YOU PUT IT THAT WAY.

09:20.935 --> 09:22.311
- DID I FORGET TO FLOSS?

09:22.395 --> 09:25.273
- I'M GOING TO HAVE TO MOVE IT
IF IT KEEPS DOING THAT.

09:27.275 --> 09:29.235
THAT'S ANOTHER REASON
WHY I BROUGHT YOU HERE.

09:29.318 --> 09:32.697
I WANTED TO SHOW YOU THIS.

09:39.120 --> 09:41.622
- THE CUP.

09:41.706 --> 09:42.915
I THOUGHT IT HAD BEEN DESTROYED.

09:42.999 --> 09:44.083
- IT'S INDESTRUCTIBLE.

09:44.166 --> 09:44.917
- I WISH THEY MADE FRIENDS
LIKE THAT.

09:45.001 --> 09:46.836
- AMBER.

09:46.919 --> 09:48.671
- I BROKE TWO OVER THE SUMMER.

09:48.754 --> 09:50.006
ONE OF THEM FELL IN THE POOL,

09:50.089 --> 09:52.049
AND THE OTHER ONE
GOT RUN OVER BY THE LIMO.

09:53.092 --> 09:54.552
IS THAT THE CUP?

09:54.635 --> 09:56.679
IS IT SIBUNA?
IS IT STARTING AGAIN?

09:56.762 --> 10:00.141
- NO, AND WHY DID YOU
FOLLOW ME UP HERE?

10:00.224 --> 10:02.435
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE A DATE.

10:02.518 --> 10:05.062
- OH, SWEET.

10:05.146 --> 10:08.107
WEIRD, BUT SWEET.

10:12.778 --> 10:14.572
- OKAY, WE'RE GOOD.

10:18.284 --> 10:22.246
MAYBE WE SHOULD JUST GO.

10:22.330 --> 10:25.166
WE DON'T WANT VICTOR
TO CATCH US UP HERE AGAIN.

10:25.249 --> 10:26.208
- THREE'S A CROWD.

10:26.292 --> 10:27.543
I GET IT.

10:27.626 --> 10:30.087
MY BAD.

10:45.269 --> 10:48.981
[eerie violin music]

10:49.065 --> 10:57.073
♪ ♪

11:13.339 --> 11:21.389
♪ ♪

11:35.111 --> 11:36.112
[knock at door]

11:36.195 --> 11:38.781
- [muffled]
I'LL BE OUT IN A MINUTE.

11:43.577 --> 11:46.664
[eerie whispering]

11:54.213 --> 11:55.965
AMBER?

11:58.050 --> 12:00.052
[suspenseful music]

12:00.136 --> 12:08.060
♪ ♪

12:08.144 --> 12:08.602
[shrieks]

12:08.686 --> 12:10.271
- OH! SORRY.

12:10.354 --> 12:11.730
I-I THOUGHT YOU WERE AMBER.

12:11.814 --> 12:12.523
- ALFIE--WHAT?

12:12.606 --> 12:15.317
- I WAS TRYING TO APOLOGIZE.

12:15.401 --> 12:16.861
FOR YESTERDAY?

12:16.944 --> 12:18.571
- WITH A SKELETON?

12:20.072 --> 12:21.073
- TOO MUCH?

12:21.157 --> 12:22.241
- A LITTLE BIT.

12:22.324 --> 12:23.909
- HMM.

12:39.049 --> 12:41.844
[knock at door]

12:41.927 --> 12:43.304
- THIS WAS PUSHED UNDER THE DOOR
FOR YOU, VICTOR.

12:43.387 --> 12:45.890
HAND-DELIVERED.

12:45.973 --> 12:47.558
- OH?

12:53.856 --> 12:56.066
- HAVE YOU THOUGHT ANY MORE
ABOUT WHAT I SAID?

12:56.150 --> 12:59.236
ABOUT TURNING THE ATTIC
INTO A SPARE BEDROOM?

12:59.320 --> 13:00.821
IT'D BE REALLY USEFUL.

13:00.905 --> 13:02.781
YOU KNOW, WHEN FRIENDS
AND RELATIVES COME TO STAY,

13:02.865 --> 13:03.866
LIKE NINA'S GRAN.

13:03.949 --> 13:05.701
- YES, YES, YES. WHATEVER.
JUST...

13:05.784 --> 13:06.702
- REALLY?

13:06.785 --> 13:08.621
SO I'LL START
CLEARING IT OUT?

13:08.704 --> 13:11.457
- YES, WHATEVER.
PLEASE GO.

13:16.670 --> 13:19.715
THERE IS HOPE YET, CORBIERE.

13:26.514 --> 13:27.890
- WHAT'S THIS?

13:27.973 --> 13:31.268
YOU MAY AS WELL GIVE ME
ACTUAL PEANUTS.

13:31.352 --> 13:32.603
- TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT.

13:32.686 --> 13:34.396
- WE AGREED.
HALF YOUR ALLOWANCE.

13:34.480 --> 13:35.731
- NO, YOU AGREED.

13:35.814 --> 13:36.398
I DID NOT.

13:36.482 --> 13:38.275
- HARDBALL IT IS, THEN.

13:38.359 --> 13:39.735
PREPARE TO LOSE.

13:39.818 --> 13:42.321
- I REFUSE TO BE BLACKMAILED
BY YOU ANYMORE.

13:42.404 --> 13:43.656
DO YOUR WORST.

13:43.739 --> 13:44.823
- FIGHTING TALK.

13:44.907 --> 13:46.033
YOU'VE GOT SASS, CLARKE.

13:46.116 --> 13:47.910
I LIKE THAT.

13:47.993 --> 13:49.828
SEE YOU LATER, LOSER.

13:56.710 --> 13:58.003
- OH, VICTOR.

13:58.087 --> 13:59.255
OH.

13:59.338 --> 14:02.341
- THE COMMISSION FOR ANCIENT
TREASURES AND ARTIFACTS.

14:02.424 --> 14:04.760
THE MAN IN CHARGE
IS A FRIEND OF YOURS, IS HE NOT?

14:04.843 --> 14:07.096
- GUSTAV ZIESTACK
IS MORE OF AN OLD COLLEAGUE.

14:07.179 --> 14:08.180
WHY DO YOU ASK?

14:10.516 --> 14:13.602
"SECURE THE EXHIBITION.
FIND THE BOOK OF ISIS."

14:13.686 --> 14:14.979
AN ANONYMOUS NOTE?

14:15.062 --> 14:15.896
- YOUR FRIEND...
- GUSTAV.

14:15.980 --> 14:18.065
- GUSTAV
IS LOOKING FOR A VENUE

14:18.148 --> 14:20.985
TO HOST THE TREASURES OF EGYPT
EXHIBITION.

14:21.068 --> 14:24.613
CALL HIM AND CONVINCE HIM
TO HOST IT HERE.

14:24.697 --> 14:25.948
- WHAT?

14:26.031 --> 14:29.702
- "SECURE THE EXHIBITION.
FIND THE BOOK OF ISIS."

14:29.785 --> 14:31.537
- VICTOR, I WANT NOTHING MORE
TO DO WITH THIS.

14:31.620 --> 14:33.664
- CALL HIM.

14:33.747 --> 14:34.957
I WANT THAT BOOK.

14:43.132 --> 14:46.176
- DUDE, I'M FLUNKING
THESE AMBER GIFTS.

14:46.260 --> 14:50.806
I NEED TO GET SOMETHING
THAT'S ROMANTIC BUT NOT LETHAL.

14:58.814 --> 15:01.942
- WHAT, UH--
IS THAT A PHOTO?

15:02.026 --> 15:03.444
- WHAT PHOTO?

15:03.527 --> 15:07.031
- WELL, THE ONE YOU'RE HOLDING
AND I'M POINTING AT.

15:07.114 --> 15:10.159
- THIS IS A PICTURE
OF MY GIRLFRIEND.

15:10.242 --> 15:11.243
[laughter]

15:11.327 --> 15:13.454
- GIRLFRIEND.
- YOU HAD A GIRLFRIEND?

15:13.537 --> 15:14.830
- YEAH, I--

15:14.913 --> 15:16.040
SHE DUMPED ME LIKE A SHOE.

15:16.123 --> 15:17.458
I CAN'T STAND THE SIGHT OF HER.

15:27.885 --> 15:28.594
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

15:28.677 --> 15:30.846
- CLEARING THIS PLACE OUT.

15:30.929 --> 15:32.806
- WHAT?
- YOU SAID I COULD.

15:32.890 --> 15:33.265
GUEST BEDROOM.

15:33.349 --> 15:35.434
- OH.

15:37.728 --> 15:39.688
DON'T TOUCH ANYTHING
THIS SIDE OF THE ROOM.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.649
I'LL TAKE THAT
DOWN TO THE CELLAR LATER.

15:41.732 --> 15:44.526
ANYTHING THAT SIDE CAN GO.

15:44.610 --> 15:46.654
AH, NO.

15:46.737 --> 15:50.199
APART FROM THAT...

15:50.282 --> 15:53.369
- THAT'S JUST
A BIT OF BROKEN DOLL.

15:53.452 --> 15:55.412
OKAY.

16:00.501 --> 16:02.419
- SHAME YOU COULDN'T COME
LAST NIGHT.

16:02.503 --> 16:04.004
THE MOVIE WAS AMAZING.

16:04.088 --> 16:05.464
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

16:05.547 --> 16:07.299
WELL, WE HAD A GREAT TIME
LOOKING AT GRAN'S PHOTOS.

16:07.383 --> 16:08.550
DIDN'T WE, FABIAN?

16:08.634 --> 16:10.052
- YEAH, YEAH.

16:10.135 --> 16:12.513
NO, WHO DOESN'T LOVE LOOKING
AT SOMEONE ELSE'S HOLIDAY?

16:12.596 --> 16:14.556
- JUST WAIT TILL SHE STARTS
READING YOU HER POEMS.

16:14.640 --> 16:16.058
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

16:16.141 --> 16:18.227
[laughter]

16:18.310 --> 16:20.479
- IS THAT JEROME?

16:20.562 --> 16:21.814
OH.

16:21.897 --> 16:22.981
- HE MAKES A REAL PRETTY LADY.

16:23.065 --> 16:26.610
- AND I HAVE PLENTY MORE
WHERE THAT CAME FROM.

16:26.694 --> 16:29.405
HERE WE HAVE MY BROTHER,
JEROME,

16:29.488 --> 16:31.073
SITTING ON HIS POTTY,
AGE TWO.

16:31.156 --> 16:34.868
JEROME CRYING ON SANTA'S KNEE,
AGE 11.

16:34.952 --> 16:36.286
MY BROTHER--

16:36.370 --> 16:37.871
- POPPY!
- OH, HI, GERBIL.

16:37.955 --> 16:39.915
DO YOU REMEMBER THE TIME
YOU DRESSED UP AS A GIRL?

16:39.998 --> 16:41.458
- THEY MADE ME DO IT.
THEY MADE ME DO IT.

16:41.542 --> 16:42.918
IT WAS A SCHOOL PLAY.

16:43.001 --> 16:44.795
IT'S A KIND OF CHRISTMAS
TRADITION OVER HERE, NINA.

16:44.878 --> 16:47.506
- HEY, NO NEED
TO JUSTIFY YOURSELF TO ME.

16:47.589 --> 16:49.717
- YOU NEVER TOLD US
YOU HAD A KID SISTER.

16:49.800 --> 16:51.885
- THAT'S BECAUSE I REFUSE
TO ACKNOWLEDGE SHE EXISTS.

16:51.969 --> 16:52.928
TAKE IT DOWN NOW.

16:53.011 --> 16:53.303
- NO CHANCE.

16:53.387 --> 16:55.180
GET OFF.

16:55.264 --> 16:56.932
- BAG.
- GIVE IT BACK.

16:57.015 --> 16:59.268
- DO THE CRIME,
YOU PAY THE FINE.

16:59.351 --> 17:00.436
- JEROME,
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO BE SO MEAN?

17:00.519 --> 17:02.646
- AND TALL?

17:02.730 --> 17:03.856
- WHAT IS GOING ON OUT HERE?

17:03.939 --> 17:06.191
HAVEN'T ANY OF YOU
GOT CLASSES TO GO TO?

17:06.275 --> 17:07.025
[claps]

17:08.277 --> 17:11.905
AH, WHO IS RESPONSIBLE
FOR THIS?

17:14.407 --> 17:16.952
- I AM.

17:17.035 --> 17:19.079
- WELL, CLARKE,
TAKE IT DOWN IMMEDIATELY.

17:19.163 --> 17:23.040
WE'RE EXPECTING A VERY IMPORTANT
VISITOR THIS AFTERNOON.

17:24.752 --> 17:26.336
- I'LL SAY THANKS
IF YOU GIVE ME BACK MY PHONE.

17:26.420 --> 17:29.214
- LATER.

17:29.298 --> 17:30.048
LOSER.

17:52.237 --> 17:54.656
- AND IT'S DEFINITELY
BETTER TODAY.

17:54.740 --> 17:56.116
- OF COURSE.
- YES, AMBER.

17:56.200 --> 17:57.868
- HOW MANY MORE TIMES?

17:57.951 --> 17:58.452
- TRUDY'S
CLEARING OUT THE ATTIC.

17:58.535 --> 18:00.871
- WHAT?

18:00.954 --> 18:02.998
- I JUST SAW HER JUNKING THE OLD
DOLLHOUSE YOU LIKED, AMBER.

18:03.081 --> 18:04.291
- NO!
I WAS GOING TO ASK FOR THAT.

18:07.127 --> 18:08.170
- WHAT ABOUT THE CUP?

18:08.253 --> 18:10.756
- IT SHOULD BE SAFE,
SHOULDN'T IT?

18:10.839 --> 18:12.424
- I HOPE SO.

18:12.508 --> 18:13.509
I'LL CHECK ON IT TONIGHT.

18:13.592 --> 18:15.010
- YEAH.

18:27.105 --> 18:29.149
- HEY! HEY, STOP!
YOU'VE GOT MY DOLLHOUSE.

18:34.112 --> 18:35.864
- HE'S GOT A SISTER.

18:35.948 --> 18:37.699
- POPPY?
YEAH, SHE STARTED THIS TERM.

18:37.783 --> 18:40.619
- WHY IS JEROME ALWAYS
SO SECRETIVE ABOUT EVERYTHING?

18:40.702 --> 18:41.703
- I KNOW.

18:41.787 --> 18:44.039
I MEAN, WHO KEEPS A SISTER
A SECRET?

18:44.122 --> 18:45.082
WEIRD.

18:45.165 --> 18:46.875
- NOT AS WEIRD AS JEROME
IN THE DRESS.

18:46.959 --> 18:47.876
- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

18:47.960 --> 18:49.378
I MEAN, I TELL HIM EVERYTHING,

18:49.461 --> 18:51.255
EVEN SOME STUFF I DEFINITELY
SHOULD'VE HELD BACK,

18:51.338 --> 18:54.174
LIKE A FEAR OF RED DOORS
AND OLIVES.

18:54.258 --> 18:55.926
- AND HERE WE HAVE
THE DRAMA STUDIO.

18:56.009 --> 18:58.178
GOOD AFTERNOON, EVERYONE.

18:58.262 --> 19:00.305
all:
GOOD AFTERNOON, MR. SWEET.

19:00.389 --> 19:01.515
- AND HAS MR. SWEET
FILLED YOU IN

19:01.598 --> 19:05.477
ON THE HISTORY
OF THE ANUBIS ESTATE, GUSTAV?

19:05.561 --> 19:08.480
IT REALLY IS
QUITE, QUITE FASCINATING.

19:08.564 --> 19:11.567
- THE FROBISHER-SMYTHES
ONCE OWNED IT, DIDN'T THEY?

19:11.650 --> 19:12.776
- THAT'S RIGHT.

19:12.860 --> 19:14.278
- AND MOVING ON.
THANK YOU.

19:16.697 --> 19:17.698
[laughter]

19:17.781 --> 19:20.492
- WHAT WAS THAT?

19:20.576 --> 19:23.495
- I DON'T KNOW,
BUT DID YOU GUYS SEE VICTOR?

19:23.579 --> 19:26.039
HE WAS PRACTICALLY BOWING.

19:26.123 --> 19:28.458
"QUITE, QUITE FASCINATING,
GUSTAV."

19:28.542 --> 19:30.752
- "GUSTAV, WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE
MY PIN COLLECTION?"

19:30.836 --> 19:32.421
- "GUSTAV,
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET MY RAVEN."

19:32.504 --> 19:36.508
- "IT'S 10:00.
I WANT YOU HEAR A PIN DROP."

19:36.592 --> 19:41.305
[laughter]

19:52.316 --> 19:55.694
- "TO AMBER,
I KNOW YOU SAID NO MORE GIFTS,

19:55.777 --> 19:57.779
"BUT I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT LIKE THIS ONE.

19:57.863 --> 19:59.489
ALFIE."

19:59.573 --> 20:00.908
- DO YOU LIKE IT?

20:00.991 --> 20:02.034
- I LOVE IT.

20:02.117 --> 20:03.952
- DO I PASS THE FIRST TEST?

20:04.036 --> 20:07.080
- ONLY IF YOU MAKE ME
MOCCO-CHOCOLATA-CCINO.

20:08.457 --> 20:10.125
- WITH SPRINKLES.
[laughs]

20:10.208 --> 20:11.960
- [gasps]

20:16.882 --> 20:18.634
FIRST TEST PASSED.

20:18.717 --> 20:21.386
- YES.

20:32.314 --> 20:33.440
- [gasps]
THE CUP.

20:37.402 --> 20:40.322
[eerie music]

20:40.405 --> 20:47.996
♪ ♪

20:48.080 --> 20:50.165
[eerie whispering]

21:30.956 --> 21:32.874
[sighs]
OKAY.

21:32.958 --> 21:34.418
IT'S STILL HERE.

21:37.087 --> 21:40.048
- HOW LONG I HAVE WAITED,

21:40.132 --> 21:42.551
LIKE ISIS WAITED FOR OSIRIS.

21:42.634 --> 21:46.388
YOU HAVE FREED ME, CHOSEN ONE.

21:50.684 --> 21:52.728
- WHO ARE YOU?
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

21:52.811 --> 21:57.441
- THE DAY WILL COME
WHEN EVERYONE WILL KNOW MY NAME.

21:57.524 --> 21:59.776
FIND IT, BRING IT,

21:59.860 --> 22:03.488
AND YOU SHALL WEEP TEARS
OF GOLD.

22:03.572 --> 22:05.615
- FIND WHAT?

22:05.699 --> 22:08.577
- THE MASK OF ANUBIS, CHILD.

22:08.660 --> 22:10.996
FIND IT BEFORE ANYONE ELSE...

22:12.456 --> 22:15.792
OR FORFEIT YOUR LIFE.
